        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 2:44PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
southwestern Pueblo, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pueblo, Pueblo Airport, Boone, Salt Creek, Blende, Avondale, Pueblo
Depot, and Pueblo Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
